<Review>Now, lemme tell ya, this place - wowee - this place is something else.

Didn't expect much going on, place was pretty much empty. But with a name like Zaytoon, you know something must be up.

Good vibes in the store - i order the fallafel deluxe. Side of pickles because I'm feeling dangerous.

Food came out in like 5 minutes and my oh my, this has got to be the biggest wrap in SF. SIZE MATTERS.

Tasted fantastic.

We also got fries. Fries were popping.

Pickles were popping.

Service was great - we got there late without realizing and they stayed open for us.

Zaytoon was popping.

Outdoor seating was a little sketch - table was so far out into the street I thought I was gonna get hit by a car a couple times, but hey - what's dinner without a little thrill?< /Review>< name>
Nolan Gray</name>

<Date>1583631793900<//Date><Rate>4< /Rate>< Text>
Their lamb platter had a variety of flavors which makes this place taste unique and authentic. It may seem pricey at first since it is $13 a plate (as of 03/2020) but it is a lot of food and it was enough to fill me up. The lamb had a lot of the lamb fat smell which does not smell very good to me but if you do like it, good for you. The seasoned onions and cucumber tomato salad are fantastic though. I just wish that the price was lower but given the location it might not be possible.< /Text>

My favorite delivery meal in San Francisco is their Mezze platter. The portions are generous enough for two meals and the food is delicious: hummus, baba ganoush,  two large tasty falafels with tahini sauce on the side, cucumber tomato salad with a big scoop of feta, a dollop of tabouli, dolmas, pickled red onions, pickles, olives and two excellent, warm big pitas. Really great food!< /review>

< Text>
WE GOT A LEAKER!! Lol. Leaking, and spray liner are lifting up a few months out of warranty. Make sure you You keep all of your paper work on these boxes. < Review>
The bakery makes both sweet and savory treats - custard tarts, small sandwiches and buns stuffed with cheeses and meats. All items are $1-3 each. It's a great place to stop for a quick bite and relax, or load up on treats while you're in Chinatown.

< Text>
Wonderful! I wasn't aware when ordering that they used UPS to ship and I panicked because I had put my P.O. box as my shipping address. I emailed the *incredible* Milk Jar family to ask if they knew how I could fix this and they emailed back within minutes, explaining that they had shipped using USPS since I had given them my P.O. box. I got the package a little later than expected (I work weekends and the post office was closed when I went after work on Saturday), and although I got into my goodie box a few days later than anticipated, I'm still incredibly impressed. The packaging is so cute, and the cookies are still soft. From the customer service, to the packaging, to the actual product, I'm beyond happy with my purchase. If I could give more than five stars, I definitely would. Thank you, Milk Jar!!! üòÄ< /Text>

< Text>
Quaint cookie and ice cream shop with very friendly staff. Came here after dinner on a Friday night with a friend, and we were glad to have done so. You order and pay at the counter before grabbing a seat. There‚Äôs various flavors of cookies and although they all looked appealing, we went with a classic chocolate chip cookie. It was dense and generous with the chocolate chips. It was on the chewier side and my friend ordered some milk to go alongside it. We also got a scoop of the Cookie Monster ice cream on the side which the cashier let me sample beforehand. It had cookie dough and Oreos mixed into blue ice cream and I thought it wasn‚Äôt too sweet. They have ice cream sandwiches available as well that you can customize. The girl working was very friendly and smiley. The other worker also proactively filled the water dispenser (located next to the hallway where the bathroom is) after hearing me say that it was out of water. They play old-timey music and it‚Äôs a cozy atmosphere with cute decor. Overall a comfy place to hang and eat some cookies!<//Text>

Great little cookie shop! The cookies are big and really good, although expensive. $3 per cookie but if you buy 5, the sixth is free. They also sell bottles of chocolate and normal milk, which are equally delicious, as well as ice cream. I recommend caramel pecan, chocolate chip, or white raspberry.

For parking, you can sometimes find it in Wilshire, but I‚Äôd recommend parking on one of the cross streets, like Cochran, and walking a block.

< review>
I really do love milk jar cookies. They are absolutely delicious!  However, my last visit was a bit disappointing. I arrived 1hour and 10 minutes before they closed, and when I got there, I had noticed partchment paper removed from quite a selection of their more popular cookies, one being the cinnamon sugar. I also noticed they were baking cookies in the back, and assumed they were replenishing cookies. After standing in line for 15 minutes, it was my turn to order and I asked if they had any cinnamon sugar. The lady responded they were out, and since they closed soon, they weren't baking any more. I understand being out of a product. But if you are still baking cookies in the back and you still had more than hour before you closed, why wouldn't you bake more?  Overall, The cookies are delicious, the customer service...it is a hit or miss.< /review>

<Gmap_id>0x80c2b91f8be9bb93:0xf1a6aa282820c177<//Gmap_id>< review>
My review will be broken down by RESTAURANT and GRUB HUB, but together earn 4 stars.  I had ordered 4 cookies via Grub hub which were delivered on time, but I only got 3 cookies instead of 4. I called Grub hub and they reached out to the driver and restaurant, and the restaurant was the one that forgot the extra cookie although the driver was supposed to check the order before he delivered it. Grub hub offered to refund the $3 for the cookie and reimburse me for the delivery fee should I reorder a cookie but per Milk Jar Cookies, the minimum order is $10 (which is why I ordered 4 cookies to begin with @ $3/each), so ordering 1 cookie wouldn't work. The driver called me back and offered to bring me the missing cookie which he did. I really appreciated everyone's effort (restaurant, driver and GrubHub) in making this error correct. Much better experiences with Grub hub and Eat24 than UberEATS, who is constantly late and never delivers food to my hotel room.

Grubhub: 5 stars
Restaurant: 4 stars

Regarding the cookies themselves, I found them to be undercooked like other reviews mention. And I can't justify $3-5/cookie. The best cookies in my opinion are Double tree Hotel...and they only cost $1-2 for each cookie,  fresh and available 24 hours.

GRUBHUB< /review>

<rating>5<//rating>< Review>
The good: Chocolate chip cookie and same with oatmeal. Both quite good but I prefer my CCC to be a bit more brown
The better: Snickerdoodle was so very good. It's a cookie hard to ruin and this place made it extremely well.
And, The chocolate pecan caramel was sooo rich.
The best: White Chocolate chip raspberry. Real raspberries. I love this cookie in general, but here, hands down The best I've ever had.
The Beyond: The Banana split. Totally awesome. All the flavors of the dessert in a cookie. one of my absolute favorites ever< /Review>

< text>
Literally the best cookies I've had in my life<//text>
< rate>
5< /rate>
< GmapID>
0x80c2b91f8be9bb93:0xf1a6aa282820c177<//GmapID>

<Resp>None< /Resp><user_name>Juancarlo Rodriguez<//user_name></record>
</dataset><record>
<Rate>4<//Rate><Pics>None<//Pics><username>Wayne Conant<//username>< Review>
The entire theme, decor and ambiance of Milk Jar Cookies is any girl's dream! A cute and quaint cookie shop on Miracle Mile with delicious scrumptious cookies the size of your head! Ok maybe that was a little exaggerated but the cookies are huge!

My work gets Milk Jar cookies catered to our office very frequently so when I saw the cute packaging and tasted the cookies, I knew I had to check out the shop for myself! Upon entering, I felt like I stepped into a Pinterest inspired vintage rustic home with mason jars, flowers and cute furniture galore. The shop smells of fresh cookies being baked and they even have milk jugs to pair along with your treat. The cookies itself are thick, huge and very filling! Soft, chewy and full of flavor in every bite. They don't skimp on their ingredients and you can taste the freshness. They also serve Fosselman's ice cream which is the perfect pairing for a ice cream cookie sandwich!

Even though the cookies are about 3 bucks a pop, keep in mind that the size of the cookie is ginormous! TREAT YOSELF!</Review>

< username>
Celestial Cat< /username>
<Date>1534489454308< /Date><rate>5</rate><Text>I have rented storage space from a handful of companies over the years. Most places are all about the same . . . modest to modern offices, and rental spaces that consist of a metal door and ceiling, and three walls of drywall, decorated with plywood patches covering damaged drywall. They all charge close to the same rates for about the same services.

So I was skeptical when my realtor highly recommended US Storage on Foster Road in Norwalk, just because she had nothing but the highest praise for this location, where she stores her own personal stuff. If it weren't for the fact that she is also a dear friend, I would have suspected she was recommending it for a kickback.

The rent for the Public Storage room I had was going up 20% after only three months, despite the fact they had NOT indicated what I'd been paying was an introductory rate. So I knew I had to get out of there fast, and researched my friend's recommendation of US Storage online, and arranged to go in to rent a unit. I expected to see what I've always seen at storage places, so I was absolutely floored when I got there, and saw that it was everything my friend had said . . .

First impression was amazing! This place is huge, with the buildings facing the street decorated to look like pleasant housing or office parks so it doesn't look like an unsightly industrial block to mar the look of the neighborhood. Their office is modern and pleasant, and I was immediately greeted by the managers, Yvette and Filbert, who were very friendly, efficient, accommodating and informative. They did everything they could to make the transition easier, including the FREE use of their moving truck for the day!

Filbert took me out to the unit in a golf cart, and I could see their location is huge! Over 1,000 units! The area was neat and clean, and solar panels provide their electricity needs. Everything about the place told me it was well~planned and executed, corporate~run, not a franchise, and everything run to corporate standards!

THE BEST PART was seeing the unit itself! No pockmarked drywall with plywood decor! Wall to wall, floor to ceiling was clean corrugated metal walls, to keep the contents safe from being pilfered through through units! I loved that the units have ALARMS with a clever means of activation, and the doors have a locking system like nothing I've seen before, absolutely unbreakable. The unit looked brand new and well~sealed against pests.

All of this, and their prices are absolutely competitive with other companies! Now I understand my friend's excitement! Just like I was floored by my friend's recommendation, which seemed just impossible or at the very least, very exaggerated, now YOU're reading MY review and probably thinking the same thing. I assure you, prior to my friend's recommendation, I'd had NO knowledge of or affiliation with US Storage ~ Foster, and there is no monetary benefit for writing this review. I just wish I'd found them years ago, if there is anything I can do to send customers their way, AND also help YOU by recommending a great storage facility, I'm happy to do it! Life has enough complications, more things in life need to be this easy and worry~free!

:-) Have a lovely day!<//Text>< pictures>
